<HEAD>Literature Prize to Be Announced Thursday</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout to CORRECT date of Nobel will in graf 2, typo in
Stockholm in 6th pvs, `The Nobel...' No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Nobel Prize in literature will be
announced on Thursday, the Swedish Academy said today.
   Under terms of the 1896 will of dynamite inventor Afred Nobel,
the award should go to a person for outstanding, idealistic work.
   The literature prize is one of five being awarded this month.
The dates for the others are set several months in advance, but the
literature prize traditionally is announced with only a few days'
notice.
   The Nobel Prize in medicine was announced Monday and shared by
an American who performed the first successful organ transplant and
an American who pioeered bone marrow transplants.
   Joseph E. Murray of Boston and E. Donnall Thomas of Bellevue,
Wash., will share the prize, worth $704,000.
   The Nobel Peace Prize will be announced Monday in Olso, Norway,
and the prizes in chemistry and physics will be announced Oct. 17
in Stockholm.
   The Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Science, created by the
Central Bank of Sweden in 1969, will be awarded in Stockholm on
Oct. 16.
</TEXT>
